s corpse. Take this testimony to Valeron Dushire in North Freeport at the Hall of Truth, and receive your Brilliant Sword of Faith. <br><br>5) Gather up your things (hilt, testimony of truth, brilliant sword of faith, note) <br><br>* I see where the note, sword of faith come from, and testimony of truth are from... but where do you get the hilt (I am guessing it is from one of the steps above but not sure).<br><br>and take them to Hayle in Paw. To open his cell, there are a couple levers a few steps from the cell door. Flip both of them, and make sure you have someone stay outside to open the cell for you when you're ready to leave. Hand in all of these components to Hayle (hilt, testimony of truth, brilliant sword of faith, note), and receive your Soulfire! <br><br>*IMPORTANT NOTE* Your faction MUST be at least Kindly to the Rodcet Nife Paladin/Cleric guild in Qeynos. To do this, have a friend of yours create a newbie SK. Take this SK to the pool with the UFO in Qeynos. Once a Koalindl fish spawns, have them HT it and melee it. Group with them, but do NOT heal them or help melee the fish. Loot the fish once it is dead. Hand it in to Enik Ruklin (wanders near or swims in the pool) and you'll get great faction. Just keep repeating this, and avoid waiting by just having the SK attack Enik and get killed. Get them bound right near the pool if you can. You must be at least amiably to the guild for this to work in the first place. You can reach amiable faction by handing in bone chips/gold to Lashun Novashine. He wanders in the newbie grounds near Qeynos Hills. Once you're kindly, head off to Paw! <br>Kaldaas<br>46th Paladin<br>Divide et Impera<br>Bristlebane Server<br><br><br>Edited by: Kaldaas DeI at: 3/18/01 4:24:15 pm<br><br>Thanks! <p>Bllack Ader - Dr00d in Agony. Arf!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uekimemsti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ekime